@@ -0,0 +1,125 @@
+# tablesmith
+
+A lightweight, scriptable pipeline engine for transforming tabular data.  
+Pure Python standard library — no external dependencies.
+
+## Install
+
+```bash
+pip install -e .
+```
+
+## Quick start
+
+```bash
+# Filter and select columns
+tablesmith data.csv --filter 'age > 30' --select name,age
+
+# Sort and limit
+tablesmith data.json --sort salary:desc --head 10
+
+# Group and aggregate
+tablesmith sales.csv --group-by region --agg 'revenue:sum,revenue:mean'
+
+# Join two files
+tablesmith orders.csv --join customers.csv --join-on customer_id=id --join-how left
+
+# Convert formats
+tablesmith data.csv -o data.json
+tablesmith data.json -o data.jsonl
+
+# Pipe from stdin
+cat data.csv | tablesmith --filter 'status == "active"' -f json
+```
+
+## Supported formats
+
+CSV, TSV, JSON (array of objects), and JSONL — auto-detected from file extension.  
+Override with `-F` (input) or `-f` (output).
+
+## Inline operations
+
+Operations are applied in this order: filter → rename → join → select → group → sort → head/tail → describe → count.
+
+| Flag | Description | Example |
+|------|-------------|---------|
+| `--filter EXPR` | Filter rows (repeatable) | `--filter 'age > 30'` |
+| `--select COLS` | Pick columns | `--select name,email` |
+| `--rename MAP` | Rename columns | `--rename old:new,x:y` |
+| `--sort SPEC` | Sort rows | `--sort age:desc,name` |
+| `--group-by COLS` | Group rows | `--group-by dept` |
+| `--agg SPEC` | Aggregations | `--agg salary:mean,id:count` |
+| `--join FILE` | Join with file | `--join other.csv` |
+| `--join-on SPEC` | Join key | `--join-on id` or `--join-on a=b` |
+| `--join-how TYPE` | Join type | `--join-how left` |
+| `--head N` | First N rows | `--head 5` |
+| `--tail N` | Last N rows | `--tail 5` |
+| `--count` | Count rows | |
+| `--describe` | Column stats | |
+
+## Filter expressions
+
+```
+age > 30
+name == "Alice"
+status != "inactive"
+salary >= 50000 and department == "Engineering"
+name contains "smith"
+name startswith "A"
+city endswith "ton"
+age is null
+age is not null
+status in ("active", "pending")
+(age > 25) or (role == "admin")
+not active
+`column with spaces` > 10
+```
+
+## Pipeline files
+
+For complex multi-step transforms, define a pipeline in JSON:
+
+```json
+{
+  "steps": [
+    {"op": "filter", "expr": "age > 18"},
+    {"op": "rename", "columns": "name:full_name"},
+    {"op": "select", "columns": "full_name,age,dept"},
+    {"op": "group", "by": "dept", "agg": "age:mean,age:count"},
+    {"op": "sort", "by": "age_mean:desc"}
+  ]
+}
+```
+
+Run it:
+
+```bash
+tablesmith data.csv --pipeline transform.json -o result.csv
+```
+
+### Pipeline operations
+
+| op | Required fields | Optional |
+|----|----------------|----------|
+| `filter` | `expr` | |
+| `select` | `columns` | |
+| `rename` | `columns` | |
+| `sort` | `by` | |
+| `group` | `by`, `agg` | |
+| `join` | `file`, `on` | `how` |
+| `head` | | `n` (default 10) |
+| `tail` | | `n` (default 10) |
+| `count` | | |
+| `describe` | | |
+
+## Type inference
+
+Types are inferred automatically from data values:
+- Integers: `"42"` → `42`
+- Floats: `"3.14"` → `3.14`
+- Booleans: `"true"` / `"false"`
+- Null: empty string, `"null"`, `"none"`, `"na"`, `"n/a"`, `"nan"`, `"-"`
+
+## Aggregation functions
+
+`sum`, `mean`/`avg`, `min`, `max`, `count`, `first`, `last`
